[0.000, "o", "d ADO can't call ConnectRPC \u001b[39m        \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mnatively. These need to be raw HTTP handlers on the existing mux. Also, the various webhooks should funnel their input into a \u001b[39m   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255msingle handling chain - provider-specific concerns like signatures stay at the edge, then normalize into a common event type.\u001b[39m    \u001b[49m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[1C\u001b[39mGood\u001b[1Ccorrection.\u001b[1CUpdated\u001b[1Cscope:\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[2C\u001b[1mScope\u001b[1CIn\u001b[1C(revised)\u001b[22m:\r\r\n\u001b[2C-\u001b[1CRaw\u001b[1CHTTP\u001b[1Chandlers\u001b[1Con\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cexisting\u001b[1Cmux\u001b[1C(not\u001b[1CConnectRPC\u001b[1C—\u001b[1Cexternal\u001b[1Csystems\u001b[1Ccan't\u001b[1Ccall\u001b[1CConnect\u001b[1Cnatively)\r\r\n\u001b[2C-\u001b[1CProvider-specific\u001b[1Cedge\u001b[1Cconcerns:\u001b[1Csignature\u001b[1Cverification,\u001b[1Cpayload\u001b[1Cparsing\u001b[1C—\u001b[1Ceach\u001b[1Cprovider\u001b[1Cowns\u001b[1Cits\u001b[1Cedge\r\r\n\u001b[2C-\u001b[1CNormalize\u001b[1Cto\u001b[1Ca\u001b[1Ccommon\u001b[1Cinternal\u001b[1Cevent\u001b[1Ctype\u001b[1Cafter\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cedge\r\r\n\u001b[2C-\u001b[1CSingle\u001b[1Cdownstream\u001b[1Chandling\u001b[1Cchain:\u001b[1Ccommon\u001b[1Cevent\u001b[1C→\u001b[1Cspec/slice\u001b["]
